                  <provenance when="1568">‘<persName key="person_4632" role="fmo">Roberti
                        Tiasi</persName> liber ex donatione <persName key="person_4633" role="fmo"
                        >Nicolai Lisardi</persName> Seruienti pictoris clementissimi principis
                     Domine Elizabethe Anglie Regine Anno redemptionis nostre 1568’, above an
                     elaborate RT monogram (<locus from="122v" to="122v">fol. 122<hi
                           rend="superscript">v</hi></locus>). Nicholas Lyzarde (d. 1571) was indeed
                     a royal sergeant-painter under four monarchs (see the brief entry in
                           <bibl><title>DNB</title></bibl>); we have been unable to identity
                     Tias.</provenance>
